\par 
\par In the grave bodily, but in Hades with Thy soul as God; in Paradise with the thief, and on the throne with the Father and the Spirit wast Thou Who fillest all things, O Christ the Inexpressible. How life-giving,
 how much more beautiful than Paradise and truly more resplendent than any royal palace hath Thy tomb appeared, O Christ, the source of our resurrection. 
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s32\ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\keep\nowidctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid1252062 \rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af0\afs28\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\fs28\cf6\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 
\ai0\af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid1252062\charrsid1252062 Then taking the veils from the holy diskos and the holy chalice, he layeth them to one side of the al
tar (in current practice, each is unfolded, and placed on the right and left side of the holy table, over the red cloth and under the cross on each side.) And taking the aer from the deacon's shoulder, and having censed it, he covereth the Holy Gifts ther
ewith, saying:
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s41\ql \fi-288\li864\ri576\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin576\lin864\itap0\pararsid3804313 \rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs36\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f1\fs36\cf15\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs32\insrsid1252062\charrsid3804313 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af1\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\i\fs28\insrsid1252062 Priest:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs32\insrsid1252062\charrsid3804313 
 The noble Joseph, having taken Thy most pure Body down from the Tree and wrapped It in pure linen and covered It with spices, laid It in a new tomb. 
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s32\ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\keep\nowidctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid1252062 \rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af0\afs28\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\fs28\cf6\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 
\ai0\af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid1252062\charrsid1252062 And taking the censer from the hand of the deacon, he censeth the Holy Gifts thrice, saying:
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s41\ql \fi-288\li864\ri576\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin576\lin864\itap0\pararsid3804313 \rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs36\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f1\fs36\cf15\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs32\insrsid1252062\charrsid3804313 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af1\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\i\fs28\insrsid1252062 Priest:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs32\insrsid1252062\charrsid3804313 
 Do good, O Lord, in Thy good pleasure unto Sion, and let the walls of Jerusalem be builded. Then shalt Thou be pleased with a sacrifice of righteousness, with oblation and whole-burnt offerings. Then shall they offer bullocks upon Thine altar.
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s32\ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\keep\nowidctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid1252062 \rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af0\afs28\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\fs28\cf6\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 
\ai0\af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid1252062\charrsid1252062 The holy doors and curtain are closed.
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s18\qc \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\sbauto1\saauto1\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid16656510 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 
\fs24\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\i\fs32\cf6\insrsid1252062\charrsid16656510 \page }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\i\fs32\cf6\insrsid16656510\charrsid16656510 
The Litany of Supplication
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s18\ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\sbauto1\saauto1\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\i\fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860 Deacon or Priest:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860  Let us complete our prayer unto the Lord. 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\i\fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860 Choir:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860  Lord, have mercy.
\par --For the precious gifts set forth, let us pray to the Lord. 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\i\fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860 Choir:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860  Lord, have mercy.
\par --For this holy temple, and for them that with faith, reverence, and the fear of God enter herein, let us pray to the Lord.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\i\fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860 Choir:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860  Lord, have mercy.
\par --That we may be delivered from all tribulation, wrath, and necessity, let us pray to the Lord.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\i\fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860 Choir:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860  Lord, have mercy. (Slowly, if there be no deacon.)
\par --Help us, save us, have mercy on us, and keep us, O God, by Thy grace.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\i\fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860 Choir:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860  Lord, have mercy.
\par --That the whole day may be perfect, holy, peaceful and sinless, let us ask of the Lord.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\i\fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860 Choir:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860  Grant this, O Lord.
\par --An angel of peace, a faithful guide, a guardian of our souls and bodies, let us ask of the Lord. 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\i\fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860 Choir:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860  Grant this, O Lord. 
\par --Pardon and remission of our sins and offences, let us ask of the Lord.
\par Choir: Grant this, O Lord.
\par --Things good and profitable for our souls, and peace for the world, let us ask of the Lord.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\i\fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860 Choir:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860  Grant this, O Lord.
\par --That we may complete the remaining time of our life in peace and repentance, let us ask of the Lord.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\i\fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860 Choir:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860  Grant this. O Lord.
\par --A Christian ending to our life, painless, blameless, peaceful, and a good defense before the dread judgment seat of Christ, let us ask.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\i\fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860 Choir:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860  Grant this, O Lord.
\par --Calling to remembrance our most holy, most pure, most blessed, glorious Lady Theotokos and Ever-Virgin Mary with all the saints, let us commit ourselves and one another and all our life unto Christ our God.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\i\fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860 Choir:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860  To Thee, O Lord.
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s32\ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\keep\nowidctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid1252062 \rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af0\afs28\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\fs28\cf6\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 
\ab\ai0\af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1252062\charrsid14706924 The deacon moves to stand before the icon of Christ while priest finisheth the prayer of Proskomedia.
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s32\qc \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\keep\nowidctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid1252062 {\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs36 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs31\b\f1\fs32\insrsid1252062\charrsid3804313 {\*\bkmkstart h30}{\*\bkmkend h30}
The Prayer of the Proskomedia (silently)}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af0\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs30\b\fs20\cf0\insrsid1252062\charrsid10162891 
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s41\ql \fi-288\li864\ri576\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin576\lin864\itap0\pararsid3804313 \rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs36\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f1\fs36\cf15\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af1\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\i\fs28\insrsid1252062 Priest:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs32\insrsid1252062\charrsid3804313  O 
Lord God Almighty, who alone art holy, Who dost accept a sacrifice of praise from them that call upon Thee with their whole heart: Accept also the supplication of us sinners, and bring it to Thy Holy Altar, and enable us to offer unto Thee both gifts and 
s
piritual sacrifices for our sins and for the errors of the people, and vouchsafe us to find grace before Thee, that our sacrifice may be acceptable unto Thee, and that the good Spirit of Thy grace may rest upon us, and upon these Gifts set forth, and upon
 all Thy people.
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s18\ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\sbauto1\saauto1\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs24\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {
\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\i\fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860 Priest:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860 
 Through the compassions of Thine Only-begotten Son, with Whom Thou art blessed, together with Thy most holy, and good, and life-creating Spirit, now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\i\fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860 Choir:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860  Amen. 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\i\fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860 Priest:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\fs32\insrsid3038447  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860 Peace be unto all.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \b\fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\i\fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860 Choir:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs32\insrsid3038447  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860 And to thy spirit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\i\fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860 Priest or Bishop:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860  Let us love one another, that with one mind we may confess:
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\i\fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860 Choir:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860  The Father, and the Son, and the Holy Spirit: }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\fs32\insrsid14179517\charrsid7024860 The}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860  Trinity, one in essence and indivisible.
\par --The doors! The doors! In wisdom let us attend.
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\qc \li0\ri0\keepn\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel0\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af0\afs24\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\fs32\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14179517 \page }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860 The Creed
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\ql \li0\ri0\sl360\slmult1\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid12401636 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860 
I believe in one God, the Father Almighty, / Maker of heaven and earth and of all things visible and invisible. / And in one Lord Jesus Christ, the Son of God, / the Only-begotten, begotten of the Father before all ages; / Light of Light, true God of tr
ue God; / begotten, not made; of one essence with the Father, by Whom all things were made; / Who for us men and for our salvation came down from the heavens, / and was incarnate of the Holy Spirit and the Virgin Mary, and became man;}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \fs32\insrsid3038447  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860 / And was crucified f
or us under Pontius Pilate, / and suffered and was buried; / And arose again on the third day according to the Scriptures; / And ascended into the heavens, and sitteth at the right hand of the Father; / And shall come again, with glory, to judge both the 
l
iving and the dead; / Whose kingdom shall have no end. / And in the Holy Spirit, the Lord, the Giver of life; Who proceedeth from the Father; / Who with the Father and the Son together is worshipped and glorified; Who spake by the prophets. / In One, Holy
, Catholic, and Apostolic Church. / I confess one baptism for the remission of sins. / I look for the resurrection of the dead, / and the life of the age to come. Amen. 
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s18\qc \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\sbauto1\saauto1\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs24\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {
\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\i\fs32\cf6\insrsid12401636\charrsid16656510 \page }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\i\fs32\cf6\insrsid11936078\charrsid16656510 The Anaphora
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s18\ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\sbauto1\saauto1\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\i\fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860 Deacon or Priest:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860  Let us stand well, let us stand with fear, let us attend, that we may offer the holy oblation in peace.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\i\fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860 Choir:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs36 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs28\f1\fs32\cf15\insrsid11936078\charrsid16656510 
A mercy of peace, a sacrifice of praise.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\i\fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860 Priest or Bishop:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860 
 The grace of our Lord Jesus Christ, and the love of God the Father, and the communion of the Holy Spirit be with you all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\i\fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860 Choir:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs36 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs28\f1\fs32\cf15\insrsid11936078\charrsid16656510 
And with thy spirit.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860 
\par --Let us lift up our hearts.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\i\fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860 Choir:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs36 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs28\f1\fs32\cf15\insrsid11936078\charrsid16656510 
We lift them up unto the Lord.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860 
\par --Let us give thanks unto the Lord.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\i\fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860 Choir:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs36 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs28\f1\fs32\cf15\insrsid11936078\charrsid16656510 
It is meet and right to worship the Father, and the Son, and the Holy Spirit: the Trinity, one in essence and indivisible. 
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s32\qc \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\keep\nowidctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid14706924 \rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af0\afs28\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\fs28\cf6\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 
\ab\af1\afs36 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs31\b\f1\fs32\insrsid14706924\charrsid3804313 The First Prayer of the Anaphora (silently)}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af0\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs30\b\fs20\cf0\insrsid14706924\charrsid10162891 
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s41\ql \fi-288\li864\ri576\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin576\lin864\itap0\pararsid3804313 \rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs36\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f1\fs36\cf15\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs24\fs28\insrsid14706924 Priest:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs32\insrsid14706924\charrsid3804313 
 It is meet and right to hymn Thee, to bless Thee, to praise Thee, to give thanks unto Thee, to worship Thee in every place of thy dominion, for Thou art God inexpressible, incomprehensible, invisible, unattainable, ev
er-existing, eternally the same, Thou and Thine Only-begotten Son and Thy Holy Spirit. Thou didst call us from nonbeing into being, and when we had fallen away, Thou didst raise us up again, and didst not cease to do all things until Thou hadst brought us
 up to heaven, and hadst bestowed upon us Thy kingdom which is\line 
to come. For all these things we give thanks unto Thee, to Thine Only-begotten Son, and to Thy Holy Spirit, for all things whereof we know, and whereof we know not; for the benefits both manifes
t and hidden which have come upon us. We give thanks unto Thee also for this service which Thou hast been pleased to accept from our hands, though there stand before Thee thousands of archangels and ten thousands of angels, the cherubim and seraphim, six-
winged, many-eyed, borne aloft on their wings.
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s32\ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\keep\nowidctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid14706924 \rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af0\afs28\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\fs28\cf6\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 
\ab\ai0\af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14706924\charrsid14706924 And here the deacon taketh the holy star from the holy diskos, maketh the sign of the cross above it, and kissing it, layeth it aside as the priest saith: 
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s18\ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\sbauto1\saauto1\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs24\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\i\fs32\insrsid16656510\charrsid16656510 Priest:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs32\insrsid16656510  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860 Singing the triumphal hymn, shouting, crying a
loud and saying:
