\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f1\fs28\cf6\insrsid11936078\charrsid8266257 During the communion of the clergy, selected hymns may be chanted, or the Prayers before Holy Communion may be read. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 
\i\f1\fs28\cf6\insrsid8266257 
\par \page }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f1\fs28\cf6\insrsid11936078\charrsid8266257 Then: 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\i\fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860 Deacon or Priest:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860  With fear of God and with faith, draw nigh.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\i\fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860 Choir:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860  Blessed is He that cometh in the name of the Lord. God is the Lord, and hath appeared unto us.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\i\fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860 Priest or Bishop:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860 
 I believe, O Lord, and I confess that Thou art truly the Christ, the Son of the living God, Who didst come into the world to save sinners, of whom I a
m chief. Moreover, I believe that this is truly Thy most pure Body, and that this is truly Thine Own Precious Blood. Wherefore, I pray Thee: Have mercy on me and forgive me my transgressions, voluntary and involuntary, in word and in deed, in knowledge an
d in ignorance. And vouchsafe me to partake without condemnation of Thy most pure Mysteries unto the remission of sins and life everlasting.
\par Of Thy Mystical Supper, O Son of God, receive me today as a communicant; for I will not speak of the Mystery to Thine enemies, nor will I give Thee a kiss as did Judas, but like the Thief do I confess Thee: Remember me, O Lord, in Thy kingdom.
\par Let not the communion of Thy Holy Mysteries be unto me for judgment or condemnation, O Lord, but for healing of soul and body.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f1\fs28\cf6\insrsid11936078\charrsid8266257 And as each person receiveth Holy Communion, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af1\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\i\f1\fs28\cf6\insrsid11936078\charrsid8266257 the priest or bishop saith}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f1\fs28\cf6\insrsid11936078\charrsid8266257 :
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860 The servant (or handmaid) of God, N., partaketh of the precious and holy Body and Blood of our Lord and God and Savior Jesus Christ unto the remission of sins and life everlasting.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\i\fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860 Choir:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860 
 Receive ye the Body of Christ; taste ye of the Fountain of Immortality. Alleluia, alleluia, alleluia.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f1\fs32\cf6\insrsid8266257 \page }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f1\fs28\cf6\insrsid8266257\charrsid8266257 After all have communed: }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 
\i\f1\fs32\cf6\insrsid8266257\charrsid8266257 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\i\fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860 Priest or Bishop:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860  Save O God, Thy people and bless Thine inheritance. 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\i\fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860 Choir:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860  We have seen the True }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs32\insrsid3045309\charrsid7024860 Light;}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs32\insrsid3045309\charrsid7024860 we}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860  have received
 the Heavenly Spirit. We have found the True Faith. We worship the Indivisible Trinity: for He hath saved us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\i\fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860 Priest or Bishop:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860  Always, now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\i\fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860 Choir:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860  Amen. Let our mouth be filled with Thy praise, O Lord, that we may hymn
 Thy glory, for Thou hast vouchsafed us to partake of Thy holy, divine, immortal and life-creating Mysteries. Keep us in Thy holiness, that we may meditate on Thy righteousness all the day long. Alleluia, alleluia, alleluia.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\i\fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860 Deacon or Priest}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860 : Aright! Havin
g partaken of the divine, holy, most pure, immortal, heavenly, and life-creating, fearful Mysteries of Christ, let us worthily give thanks unto the Lord. 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\i\fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860 Choir:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860  Lord, have mercy. 
\par --Help us, save us, have mercy on us, and keep us, O God, by Thy grace. 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\i\fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860 Choir:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860  Lord, have mercy.
\par --Having asked that the whole day may be perfect, holy, peaceful and sinless, let us commit ourselves and one another and all our life unto Christ our God. 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\i\fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860 Choir:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860  To Thee, O Lord. 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\i\fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860 Priest or Bishop:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860  For Thou art our sanctification, 
and unto Thee do we send up glory: to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit, now and ever, and unto the ages of ages.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\i\fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860 Choir:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860  Amen.
\par -- Let us depart in peace. 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\i\fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860 Choir:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860  In the name of the Lord.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\i\fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860 Deacon or Priest:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860  Let us pray to the Lord. 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\i\fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860 Choir:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860  Lord, have mercy. 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s18\qc \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\sbauto1\saauto1\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860 The Prayer Behind the Ambo:
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s18\ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\sbauto1\saauto1\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\i\fs32\ul\insrsid11936078\charrsid15560968 Priest:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860  O Lord Who dost bless them that bless Thee and sanctify them that put their trust in Thee: Save Thy people and bless Thine inheritance; preserve the fullness of Thy Church, sanctify them that love the b
eauty of Thy house; do Thou glorify them by Thy divine power, and forsake us not that hope in Thee. Give peace to Thy world, to Thy churches, to the priests, and to all Thy people. For every good gift and every perfect gift is from above, and cometh down 
from Thee, the Father of lights, and unto Thee do we send up glory and thanksgiving and worship, to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit, now and ever, and unto the ages of ages.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\i\fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860 Choir:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860  Amen. Blessed be the name of the Lord from henceforth and forever more. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \i\fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860 Thrice.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs32\insrsid3038447  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860 
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\qc \li0\ri0\keepn\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel0\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af0\afs24\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\fs32\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14179517 \page }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\cf6\insrsid11936078\charrsid15560968 Psalm 33
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860 
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s18\ql \fi720\li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\sbauto1\saauto1\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs24\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860 I will bless the Lord at all times, * His praise shall continually be in my mouth. *In the Lord shall my soul be praised; * let the meek hear and be glad. 
\par O magnify the Lord with me, * and let us exalt His name together. * I sought the Lord, and He heard me, * and delivered me from all my tribulations. 
\par Come unto Him, and be enlightened, * and your faces shall not be ashamed. * This poor man cried, and the Lord heard him, * and saved him out of all his tribulations. 
\par The angel of the Lord will encamp round about them that fear Him, * and will deliver them. * O taste and see that the Lord is good; * blessed is the man that hopeth in Him. 
\par O fear the Lord, all ye His saints; * for there is no want to them that fear Him. * Rich men have turned poor and gone hungry; * but they that seek the Lord shall not be deprived of any good thing. 
\par Come ye children, hearken unto me; * I will teach you the fear of the Lord. * What man is there that desireth life, * who loveth to see good days?
\par  Keep thy tongue from evil, * and thy lips from speaking guile. * Turn away from evil, and do good; * seek peace, and pursue it. 
\par The eyes of the Lord are upon the righteous, * and His ears are opened unto their supplication. * The face of the Lord is against them that do evil, * utterly to destroy the remembrance of them from the earth. 
\par The righteous cried, and the Lord heard them, * and He delivered them out of all their tribulations. * The Lord is nigh unto them that are of a contrite heart, * and He will save the humble of spirit. * 
\par Many are the tribulations of the righteous, * and the Lord shall deliver them out of them all. * The Lord keepeth all their bones, * not one of them shall be broken. 
\par The death of sinners is evil, * and they that hate the righteous shall do wrong. * The Lord will redeem the souls of His servants, * and none of them will do wrong that hope in Him.
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s18\ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\sbauto1\saauto1\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\i\fs32\ul\insrsid11936078\charrsid15560968 Priest or Bishop:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860  The blessing of the Lord be upon you, through His grace and love for mankind, always, now and ever, and unto the ages of ages.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\i\fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860 Choir:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860  Amen.
\par --Glory to Thee, O Christ God, our hope, glory to Thee.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\i\fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860 Choir:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs32\insrsid11936078\charrsid7024860 
